Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%container} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{12-15%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once the onion has caramelised, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%ml}, @ground coriander{1} and remaining North Indian style spice mix to the pan. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, @coconut milk{200%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, lentils and @water{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

While the dal simmers, halve the @lemon{1/2}. Once thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the dal a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and squeeze in some lemon juice. Taste and add salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed.

Spoon the dal into your #serving bowls{} and top with the roasted broccoli. Enjoy!